=============================================================================
ATTACK-PROMPT PROVENANCE AND PER-SOURCE LICENSE VERIFICATION
=============================================================================

ouija ships a hand-curated corpus of adversarial prompts in ouija/corpus/.
This NOTICE documents the provenance of those prompts and the license
verification performed for every public dataset that informed them, per the
v0.1 attribution requirement.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Summary of provenance
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
All prompt STRINGS shipped in ouija/corpus/ (injection.json, disclosure.json,
dos.json) are ORIGINALLY AUTHORED by the ouija project. They are generic,
well-known prompt-injection / disclosure / DoS *techniques* (e.g. "ignore
previous instructions", system-prompt extraction, persona-shift, delimiter
confusion) rewritten in our own words and instrumented with our own benign
detection marker (OUIJA_INJECTION_CONFIRMED). No prompt text was copied
verbatim from any external dataset.

The categories of techniques were INFORMED by the public LLM-red-teaming
literature and datasets listed below. Because no verbatim text was copied,
no third-party prompt is redistributed by ouija. Attribution is provided
regardless, for transparency and good-faith credit.

